HEADWORD: Scavenging
<hw>Scav"eng*ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <mord>of
<er>Scavenge</er>.</mord> Hence, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Internal-combustion
Engines)</fld> <def>Act or process of expelling the exhaust gases from
the cylinder by some special means, as, in many four-cycle engines, by
utilizing the momentum of the exhaust gases in a long exhaust
pipe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

